<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id4742bd2a-3a70-11f1-a967-d35dac11796a" identifier="/us/usc/t26/s7124"><num value="7124">§ 7124.</num><heading> Cross references</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I23" class="indent2 fontsize7">For criminal penalties for concealment of property, false statement, or falsifying and destroying records, in connection with any closing agreement, compromise, or offer of compromise, see section 7206.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="id4742bd2b-3a70-11f1-a967-d35dac11796a">(<ref href="/us/act/1954-08-16/ch736">Aug. 16, 1954, ch. 736</ref>, <ref href="/us/stat/68A/850">68A Stat. 850</ref>, § 7123; <ref href="/us/pl/97/258/s3/f/12">Pub. L. 97–258, § 3(f)(12)</ref>, <date date="1982-09-13">Sept. 13, 1982</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/96/1065">96 Stat. 1065</ref>; renumbered § 7124, <ref href="/us/pl/105/206/tIII/s3465/a/1">Pub. L. 105–206, title III, § 3465(a)(1)</ref>, <date date="1998-07-22">July 22, 1998</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/112/767">112 Stat. 767</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
